This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of deep networks and perceptual loss also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of texture similarity and segmentation labels suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
